abstract: >-
  Nine architectural decision records (one experimental) and four
  Business AI Quadrants recording how attribution — who authored
  the behavior, who bears its consequences, who can reconstruct its
  cause — is distributed across an autonomous AI agent system, and
  how a piece of work is routed to the architectural regime where
  that distribution operates. Extracted from the contemplative-agent
  implementation, the archived Agent Knowledge Cycle (AKC)
  governance triplet, and a five-essay narrative spine published in
  April 2026; re-expressed in harness-neutral form. ADR-0001
  Security by Absence, ADR-0002 Deterministic Prohibition at the
  Scaffolding Layer, and ADR-0003 Untrusted Content Boundary form a
  prohibition-strength hierarchy. ADR-0009 Triage Before Autonomy
  pairs with the four Business AI Quadrants (Script, Algorithmic
  Search, LLM Workflow, Autonomous Agentic Loop) as the diagnostic
  frame for routing work to the architecture preserving accountability
  distribution. Includes thesis, manifesto, glossary, lineage, a
  security-principles skill, an adoption navigator (decision tree,
  governance mapping, case studies, anti-patterns), and AI-facing
  reference files (llms.txt, llms-full.txt) per the Answer.AI
  standard.
